const e=JSON.parse('[{"title":"saddle-ai-goap","slug":"/","type":"title"},{"title":"saddle-ai-goap","slug":"/","heading":"saddle-ai-goap","anchor":"","type":"content","content":"Reusable Goal-Oriented Action Planning runtime for Bevy. The crate keeps planning definitions shared at the app level and per-agent runtime state on entities. It is intentionally project-agnostic: it does not assume a specific combat stack, navigation system, inventory model, animation graph, or state machine. Game code provides sensors, target providers, dynamic goal scoring, action validation, and action execution. For apps where planners should stay live for the full app lifetime, prefer GoapPlugin::always_on(Update). Use GoapPlugin::new(...) when activation should follow explicit schedules such as OnEnter / OnExit."},{"title":"saddle-ai-goap","slug":"/","heading":"Quick Start","anchor":"#quick-start","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"saddle-ai-goap","slug":"/","heading":"Public API","anchor":"#public-api","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"saddle-ai-goap","slug":"/","heading":"Public API","anchor":"#public-api","type":"content","content":"- Plugin: GoapPlugin - System sets: GoapSystems::{Sense, SelectGoal, Plan, Dispatch, Monitor, Cleanup, Debug} - Components: GoapAgent, GoapRuntime, GoapPlan, ActiveAction, GoapDebugSnapshot, DeferredInvalidation - Resources: GoapLibrary, GoapHooks, GoapPlannerScheduler, GoapGlobalSensorCache, GoapReservationMap - Reservation types: ReservationPolicy, ReservationEntry - Definition types: GoapDomainDefinition, GoalDefinition, ActionDefinition, SensorDefinition - Planner types: PlanningProblem, PlanningSession, GoapPlannerLimits, SelectedGoal, TargetCandidate - World-state types: WorldStateSchema, WorldKeyId, FactValue, FactCondition, FactEffect, FactPatch, TargetToken - Messages: GoalChanged, PlanStarted, PlanCompleted, PlanFailed, PlanInvalidated, ActionDispatched, ActionCancelled, ActionExecutionReport, InvalidateGoapAgent, InvalidateLocalSensors, InvalidateGlobalSensors"},{"title":"saddle-ai-goap","slug":"/","heading":"Core Model","anchor":"#core-model","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"saddle-ai-goap","slug":"/","heading":"Core Model","anchor":"#core-model","type":"content","content":"- Shared definitions, per-agent runtime: GoapLibrary stores reusable immutable-ish domain definitions; entities store only runtime state, the current goal, the active plan cursor, active action tracking, counters, and sensor timing. - Agent-centric symbolic memory: planning reads GoapWorldState, not broad ECS queries. Sensors curate the symbolic state from world data. - Target-aware actions: target providers generate TargetCandidate values per action slot, and planners evaluate each candidate as its own symbolic action variant. - Interruptible execution: planning dispatches an ActionDispatched message and waits for ActionExecutionReport messages with Running, Waiting, Success, Failure, or Cancelled. Actions marked interruptible: false defer soft invalidations (HigherPriorityGoal, SensorRefresh) until they complete; hard invalidations (TargetInvalidated, RequiredFactChanged, Manual) always interrupt immediately. - Budgeted planning: PlanningSession supports incremental A search, and GoapPlannerScheduler limits how many agents advance their planning work per frame. - Layered planner budgets: GoapDomainDefinition::withdefaultlimits(...) sets domain-wide defaults, while GoapAgentConfig::withplannerlimits(...) lets specific agents override them. - Exact-problem plan caching: GoapAgentConfig::plancachecapacity keeps recently successful plans reusable when the symbolic problem repeats. - Failed-plan retry gating: when a goal fails at a specific sensor revision, the runtime will not spam identical replans every frame; it waits for a goal change, invalidation, or newer sensed state before retrying. - Target reservations: opt-in ReservationPolicy on GoapDomainDefinition tracks which agents have claimed which targets via GoapReservationMap. Reserved targets receive a cost penalty (or are hard-blocked) during planning, preventing multiple agents from independently targeting the same entity. - hmax heuristic: the planner uses an action-relevance-aware hmax heuristic instead of a simple unsatisfied-condition count. For each goal condition, it precomputes the minimum cost among actions that can satisfy it, then returns the maximum. This is admissible and produces tighter estimates when action costs vary. - Zobrist-cached world state: GoapWorldState maintains an incrementally-updated Zobrist hash for O(1) HashMap lookups during A search, replacing per-element O(n) hashing. Domains can also be loaded from RON assets through GoapDomainAsset and GoapDomainAssetLoader."},{"title":"saddle-ai-goap","slug":"/","heading":"Replanning Policy","anchor":"#replanning-policy","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"saddle-ai-goap","slug":"/","heading":"Replanning Policy","anchor":"#replanning-policy","type":"content","content":"The runtime exposes deliberate replan triggers instead of hiding replanning inside ad-hoc execution code: - RequiredFactChanged: the current step\'s symbolic preconditions no longer match sensed state. - TargetInvalidated: the current step\'s chosen target no longer exists or fails context validation. - ActionFailed: game-side execution reported failure. - HigherPriorityGoal: goal selection found a more relevant goal than the active one. - SensorRefresh: enabled by GoapAgentConfig::replanonsensedstatechange; when no action is currently running, a sensor revision newer than the current plan invalidates stale assumptions and queues a rebuild. - GoalCompleted / GoalNoLongerValid: the active goal is done or no longer passes its validator. The default policy is conservative while an action is running: the crate keeps the action alive until it fails, succeeds, loses a required target, or loses a currently-required fact. Once the agent is between actions, a newer sensor revision can invalidate the remainder of the plan."},{"title":"saddle-ai-goap","slug":"/","heading":"Examples","anchor":"#examples","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"saddle-ai-goap","slug":"/","heading":"Crate-Local Lab","anchor":"#crate-local-lab","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"saddle-ai-goap","slug":"/","heading":"Crate-Local Lab","anchor":"#crate-local-lab","type":"content","content":"shared/ai/saddle-ai-goap/examples/lab is the richer verification surface for this crate. It keeps target loss, worker replanning, overlay diagnostics, BRP resources, and E2E scenarios inside the shared crate instead of pushing them into project-level sandboxes. E2E commands: The lab and support examples now expose live tuning through saddle-pane."},{"title":"saddle-ai-goap","slug":"/","heading":"BRP","anchor":"#brp","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"saddle-ai-goap","slug":"/","heading":"BRP","anchor":"#brp","type":"content","content":"Useful BRP commands against the lab:"},{"title":"saddle-ai-goap","slug":"/","heading":"Limitations","anchor":"#limitations","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"saddle-ai-goap","slug":"/","heading":"Limitations","anchor":"#limitations","type":"content","content":"- The crate keeps the symbolic state intentionally compact: booleans, integers, and target tokens are first-class. Rich spatial reasoning should usually stay in target providers and context validators instead of being pushed into float-heavy symbolic state. - Squad-level coordination beyond target reservations is not built in. - The runtime does not ship a genre-specific action executor. Games are expected to own the actual locomotion, animation, combat, or crafting behavior that satisfies dispatched actions."},{"title":"saddle-ai-goap","slug":"/","heading":"More Docs","anchor":"#more-docs","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"saddle-ai-goap","slug":"/","heading":"More Docs","anchor":"#more-docs","type":"content","content":"- Architecture - Configuration - Planning Model - Debugging"},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","type":"title"},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Architecture","anchor":"","type":"content","content":"saddle-ai-goap splits the runtime into three layers: 1. Shared domain definitions in GoapLibrary 2. Per-agent runtime state on GoapRuntime 3. Game-owned hooks for sensing, scoring, target selection, validation, and execution That split keeps planning data reusable while avoiding deep per-entity definition clones."},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Why Forward A*","anchor":"#why-forward-a","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Why Forward A*","anchor":"#why-forward-a","type":"content","content":"The planner uses forward A search over the agent\'s current symbolic state. This choice is deliberate: - action effects are already authored as forward symbolic mutations - target-aware action variants are easy to enumerate as concrete successor nodes - dynamic cost hooks fit naturally into successor expansion - incremental search across frames is straightforward because the open set stores future states directly Tradeoffs: - regressive planning can reason from the goal backwards with smaller branching in some domains - forward planning can expand more nodes when many actions are available early - target-heavy domains can multiply the branching factor if target providers return too many candidates The crate addresses those tradeoffs with explicit budgets: - maxnodeexpansions - maxplanlength - maxexpansionsperstep - GoapPlannerScheduler::maxagentsper_frame"},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Data Flow","anchor":"#data-flow","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Shared vs Per-Agent Storage","anchor":"#shared-vs-per-agent-storage","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Shared vs Per-Agent Storage","anchor":"#shared-vs-per-agent-storage","type":"content","content":"Shared: - GoapLibrary domain schemas, goals, actions, and sensor definitions - GoapHooks app-level sensor, scoring, validation, target, and dynamic-cost handlers - GoapGlobalSensorCache domain-scoped symbolic cache for expensive shared sensor work - GoapPlannerScheduler fairness queue and per-frame planner budget - GoapReservationMap per-domain target reservation tracking; opt-in via ReservationPolicy Per agent: - GoapAgent domain binding and per-agent config - GoapRuntime sensed state, active goal, plan cursor, active action, counters, sensor timing, failed-plan retry bookkeeping, deferred invalidation intent, reserved target tokens, and optional incremental planning session - GoapDebugSnapshot BRP-friendly current goal, plan chain, targets, invalidation reason, and counter summary Asset-authored domains load through GoapDomainAssetLoader, then register into GoapLibrary exactly like code-built domains. The planner therefore sees one normalized source of truth after load time."},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Runtime Pipeline","anchor":"#runtime-pipeline","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Runtime Pipeline","anchor":"#runtime-pipeline","type":"content","content":"The public runtime phases are:"},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`GoapSystems::Sense`","anchor":"#goapsystems-sense","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`GoapSystems::Sense`","anchor":"#goapsystems-sense","type":"content","content":"- initialize late-spawned agents - refresh global sensors on interval or invalidation - refresh local sensors on interval or invalidation - update sensed symbolic state and sensor revisions"},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`GoapSystems::SelectGoal`","anchor":"#goapsystems-selectgoal","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`GoapSystems::SelectGoal`","anchor":"#goapsystems-selectgoal","type":"content","content":"- score and validate goals - preempt current goals when a better one becomes relevant - invalidate stale plans when sensor revisions moved past the current plan and the agent is configured to replan on sensor refresh - queue planning work"},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`GoapSystems::Plan`","anchor":"#goapsystems-plan","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`GoapSystems::Plan`","anchor":"#goapsystems-plan","type":"content","content":"- dequeue up to maxagentsper_frame agents - build a PlanningProblem - advance an incremental PlanningSession - publish PlanStarted or PlanFailed - remember the sensor revision of failed plans so identical retries stay blocked until the world state or goal changes"},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`GoapSystems::Dispatch`","anchor":"#goapsystems-dispatch","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`GoapSystems::Dispatch`","anchor":"#goapsystems-dispatch","type":"content","content":"- convert the current step into ActionDispatched - create a stable ticket for execution feedback - move the agent into WaitingOnAction"},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`GoapSystems::Monitor`","anchor":"#goapsystems-monitor","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`GoapSystems::Monitor`","anchor":"#goapsystems-monitor","type":"content","content":"- consume ActionExecutionReport - invalidate plans on failed preconditions, target loss, explicit invalidations, or sensor-refresh policy - for non-interruptible actions (interruptible: false), defer soft invalidations (HigherPriorityGoal, SensorRefresh) until the action completes; process deferred invalidation on Success - complete goals when their desired conditions or completion hook says they are done"},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`GoapSystems::Cleanup`","anchor":"#goapsystems-cleanup","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`GoapSystems::Cleanup`","anchor":"#goapsystems-cleanup","type":"content","content":"- remove runtime state from entities that lost GoapAgent - reap expired target reservations based on ReservationPolicy::ttl_seconds"},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`GoapSystems::Debug`","anchor":"#goapsystems-debug","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`GoapSystems::Debug`","anchor":"#goapsystems-debug","type":"content","content":"- write a compact GoapDebugSnapshot for overlay UI, BRP, and inspection tools"},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Target-Aware Planning","anchor":"#target-aware-planning","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Target-Aware Planning","anchor":"#target-aware-planning","type":"content","content":"Actions with ActionTargetSpec do not plan against a generic anonymous target. Instead: 1. a target provider returns candidate TargetCandidate values 2. each candidate becomes a concrete PreparedActionVariant 3. context validators and dynamic cost hooks evaluate the action with that target bound 4. the chosen target is preserved on the plan step and echoed in ActionDispatched This keeps the planner symbolic while letting game code own the expensive spatial reasoning."},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Sensor Policy","anchor":"#sensor-policy","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Sensor Policy","anchor":"#sensor-policy","type":"content","content":"Sensors are first-class because the planner should reason over curated memory, not raw ECS state. - local sensors update agent-specific symbolic facts - global sensors update shared domain caches - both support interval polling plus explicit invalidation messages - sensor refreshes increment a revision counter That revision counter is what makes deliberate stale-plan invalidation possible. The planner can explain that a replan happened because symbolic memory changed, not because some hidden gameplay system silently discarded the plan."},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Heuristic and State Hashing","anchor":"#heuristic-and-state-hashing","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Heuristic and State Hashing","anchor":"#heuristic-and-state-hashing","type":"content","content":"The planner uses an hmax heuristic: for each unsatisfied goal condition, it looks up the minimum cost among actions whose effects can satisfy it (precomputed in ActionRelevanceMap), then returns the maximum of those per-condition costs. This is admissible and much tighter than a simple unsatisfied-condition count when action costs vary. GoapWorldState maintains an incrementally-updated Zobrist hash. Each mutation XORs out the old slot hash and XORs in the new one. Hash uses the cached u64 directly (O(1)), and PartialEq fast-rejects on hash mismatch before falling through to element-wise comparison. This eliminates the O(n) per-lookup cost in the planner\'s bestcosts HashMap."},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Action Interruptibility","anchor":"#action-interruptibility","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Action Interruptibility","anchor":"#action-interruptibility","type":"content","content":"Actions can be marked interruptible: false on their ActionDefinition. When a running non-interruptible action receives a soft invalidation (HigherPriorityGoal or SensorRefresh), the invalidation is stored in GoapRuntime.deferred_invalidation rather than cancelling the action immediately. Hard invalidations (TargetInvalidated, RequiredFactChanged, ActionFailed, Manual, GoalNoLongerValid) always interrupt regardless. The deferred invalidation fires when the action completes with Success. If the action fails, the failure takes priority and the deferred invalidation is discarded."},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Target Reservations","anchor":"#target-reservations","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Target Reservations","anchor":"#target-reservations","type":"content","content":"When GoapDomainDefinition.reservationpolicy is set, the planner participates in target coordination: 1. During buildplanningproblem, reserved targets owned by other agents receive a cost penalty (or are excluded with hardblock: true) 2. On plan acceptance (applysuccessfulplan), all targeted steps reserve their tokens in GoapReservationMap 3. On plan invalidation, goal completion, or agent deactivation, reservations are released 4. Stale reservations are reaped during GoapSystems::Cleanup based on ttl_seconds Because the planner scheduler processes agents sequentially, the second agent to plan always sees the first agent\'s reservations."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","type":"title"},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Configuration","anchor":"","type":"content","content":"This document covers every public tuning surface in saddle-ai-goap."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`GoapPlugin`","anchor":"#goapplugin","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`GoapPlugin`","anchor":"#goapplugin","type":"content","content":"- activateschedule schedule that initializes runtime components for newly active agents - deactivateschedule schedule that removes runtime state when planners should go offline - updateschedule schedule that runs GoapSystems::{Sense, SelectGoal, Plan, Dispatch, Monitor, Cleanup, Debug} Use alwayson for standalone examples or apps where planners never deactivate."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`GoapDomainDefinition::with_default_limits`","anchor":"#goapdomaindefinition-with-default-limits","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`GoapDomainDefinition::with_default_limits`","anchor":"#goapdomaindefinition-with-default-limits","type":"content","content":"Sets the default GoapPlannerLimits for every agent in the domain. - use this when the whole domain should share the same planning budget - agents can still opt out with GoapAgentConfig::withplannerlimits(...)"},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`GoapAgentConfig`","anchor":"#goapagentconfig","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`GoapAgentConfig`","anchor":"#goapagentconfig","type":"content","content":"Per-agent planner policy."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`planner_limits: Option<GoapPlannerLimits>`","anchor":"#planner-limits-option-goapplannerlimits","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`planner_limits: Option<GoapPlannerLimits>`","anchor":"#planner-limits-option-goapplannerlimits","type":"content","content":"Default: None - None use the domain\'s withdefaultlimits(...) value - Some(limits) override the domain default on this agent only Prefer the builder:"},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`plan_cache_capacity: usize`","anchor":"#plan-cache-capacity-usize","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`plan_cache_capacity: usize`","anchor":"#plan-cache-capacity-usize","type":"content","content":"Default: 8 Maximum number of exact-problem plan drafts retained on the agent. Set to 0 to disable plan reuse entirely."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`preempt_on_better_goal: bool`","anchor":"#preempt-on-better-goal-bool","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`preempt_on_better_goal: bool`","anchor":"#preempt-on-better-goal-bool","type":"content","content":"Default: true - true a higher-scored goal can interrupt the current goal - false the agent keeps the current goal until it completes or becomes invalid"},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`goal_switch_margin: f32`","anchor":"#goal-switch-margin-f32","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`goal_switch_margin: f32`","anchor":"#goal-switch-margin-f32","type":"content","content":"Default: 0.25 The new goal must beat the current goal by at least this much score before preemption happens. This reduces goal thrashing when two goals are nearly tied."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`replan_on_sensed_state_change: bool`","anchor":"#replan-on-sensed-state-change-bool","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`replan_on_sensed_state_change: bool`","anchor":"#replan-on-sensed-state-change-bool","type":"content","content":"Default: true - true when the agent is between actions and a newer sensor revision exists than the current plan or in-flight planning session, the runtime invalidates the stale work with PlanInvalidationReason::SensorRefresh - false the runtime keeps the current plan unless a required fact changes, a target disappears, execution fails, or a better goal wins"},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Failed-plan retry gate","anchor":"#failed-plan-retry-gate","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Failed-plan retry gate","anchor":"#failed-plan-retry-gate","type":"content","content":"saddle-ai-goap deliberately avoids retrying the exact same failed plan every frame. - after PlanFailed, the runtime records the current goal and sensor revision - while that goal and sensor revision stay unchanged, GoapSystems::SelectGoal will not immediately queue the same plan again - retries resume automatically when sensed state changes, the goal changes, or an explicit invalidation clears the stale failure record This keeps impossible goals from hammering the planner queue and inflating failure metrics."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`GoapPlannerLimits`","anchor":"#goapplannerlimits","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`GoapPlannerLimits`","anchor":"#goapplannerlimits","type":"content","content":"Per-plan search limits."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`max_node_expansions: u32`","anchor":"#max-node-expansions-u32","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`max_node_expansions: u32`","anchor":"#max-node-expansions-u32","type":"content","content":"Default: 256 Hard guardrail for the full search. When reached, planning fails with PlanningFailureReason::MaxNodeExpansions."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`max_plan_length: usize`","anchor":"#max-plan-length-usize","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`max_plan_length: usize`","anchor":"#max-plan-length-usize","type":"content","content":"Default: 8 Maximum number of symbolic actions allowed in a plan. Use this to stop runaway search in noisy action spaces."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`max_expansions_per_step: u32`","anchor":"#max-expansions-per-step-u32","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`max_expansions_per_step: u32`","anchor":"#max-expansions-per-step-u32","type":"content","content":"Default: 64 Per-frame search budget for incremental planning. Lower values spread work across more frames; higher values reduce planning latency but can spike frame time."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`SensorInterval`","anchor":"#sensorinterval","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`SensorInterval`","anchor":"#sensorinterval","type":"content","content":"Per-sensor polling cadence."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`seconds: f32`","anchor":"#seconds-f32","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`seconds: f32`","anchor":"#seconds-f32","type":"content","content":"Default via SensorInterval::default(): 0.25 - 0.0 refresh every planner frame - > 0.0 refresh only after that amount of elapsed time"},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`phase_offset: f32`","anchor":"#phase-offset-f32","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`phase_offset: f32`","anchor":"#phase-offset-f32","type":"content","content":"Default: 0.0 Offsets the first scheduled refresh. Useful for staggering large sensor populations."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`GoapPlannerScheduler`","anchor":"#goapplannerscheduler","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`GoapPlannerScheduler`","anchor":"#goapplannerscheduler","type":"content","content":"Shared planner queue resource."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`max_agents_per_frame: usize`","anchor":"#max-agents-per-frame-usize","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`max_agents_per_frame: usize`","anchor":"#max-agents-per-frame-usize","type":"content","content":"Default: 8 Number of agents whose planning work may advance in one frame. Lower it when you have many agents and want tighter frame-time control."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`queue_depth: usize`","anchor":"#queue-depth-usize","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`queue_depth: usize`","anchor":"#queue-depth-usize","type":"content","content":"Read-only runtime metric that mirrors the current queue length. The queue itself is internal; queue_depth exists so BRP, overlays, and diagnostics can inspect pressure without exposing queue internals."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Asset Loading","anchor":"#asset-loading","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Asset Loading","anchor":"#asset-loading","type":"content","content":"GoapDomainAssetLoader registers the .goap.ron extension."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Goal Definitions","anchor":"#goal-definitions","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`priority: i32`","anchor":"#priority-i32","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`priority: i32`","anchor":"#priority-i32","type":"content","content":"Base fixed-priority bias."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`relevance: Option<HookKey>`","anchor":"#relevance-option-hookkey","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`relevance: Option<HookKey>`","anchor":"#relevance-option-hookkey","type":"content","content":"Optional dynamic score hook. The final score is:"},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`validator: Option<HookKey>`","anchor":"#validator-option-hookkey","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`validator: Option<HookKey>`","anchor":"#validator-option-hookkey","type":"content","content":"Optional boolean hook used to reject a goal before planning."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`completion: Option<HookKey>`","anchor":"#completion-option-hookkey","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`completion: Option<HookKey>`","anchor":"#completion-option-hookkey","type":"content","content":"Optional boolean hook that overrides pure desired-state completion checks."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Action Definitions","anchor":"#action-definitions","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`base_cost: u32`","anchor":"#base-cost-u32","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`base_cost: u32`","anchor":"#base-cost-u32","type":"content","content":"Base symbolic action cost. The runtime clamps it to at least 1."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`dynamic_cost: Option<HookKey>`","anchor":"#dynamic-cost-option-hookkey","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`dynamic_cost: Option<HookKey>`","anchor":"#dynamic-cost-option-hookkey","type":"content","content":"Optional hook that adds a dynamic signed delta to base_cost."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`context_validator: Option<HookKey>`","anchor":"#context-validator-option-hookkey","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`context_validator: Option<HookKey>`","anchor":"#context-validator-option-hookkey","type":"content","content":"Optional hook used to reject an action variant, including target-bound variants, before planning."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`target: Option<ActionTargetSpec>`","anchor":"#target-option-actiontargetspec","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`target: Option<ActionTargetSpec>`","anchor":"#target-option-actiontargetspec","type":"content","content":"Optional target slot plus provider key. When present, the planner asks game code for candidate targets and expands one symbolic action variant per target."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`interruptible: bool`","anchor":"#interruptible-bool","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`interruptible: bool`","anchor":"#interruptible-bool","type":"content","content":"Default: true Controls whether soft invalidations are deferred when this action is running: - true plan is immediately invalidated on HigherPriorityGoal or SensorRefresh - false soft invalidations are stored in GoapRuntime.deferred_invalidation and processed when the action completes with Success Hard invalidations (TargetInvalidated, RequiredFactChanged, ActionFailed, Manual, GoalNoLongerValid) always interrupt immediately regardless of this setting. Use false for actions with side effects that must complete (animations, network calls, state mutations that cannot be rolled back)."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Debug Surface","anchor":"#debug-surface","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`GoapDebugSnapshot`","anchor":"#goapdebugsnapshot","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`GoapDebugSnapshot`","anchor":"#goapdebugsnapshot","type":"content","content":"Always attached alongside GoapRuntime. Use it when you want a compact inspection surface instead of dumping the full runtime component."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`GoapGlobalSensorCache`","anchor":"#goapglobalsensorcache","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`GoapGlobalSensorCache`","anchor":"#goapglobalsensorcache","type":"content","content":"Reflect-enabled resource holding domain-scoped symbolic caches and global sensor runtime info."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`GoapRuntime`","anchor":"#goapruntime","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`GoapRuntime`","anchor":"#goapruntime","type":"content","content":"Reflect-enabled component exposing the full runtime state, including local and global sensor timing, active action ticket, counters, last invalidation reason, deferred invalidation, and reserved target tokens."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`GoapReservationMap`","anchor":"#goapreservationmap","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`GoapReservationMap`","anchor":"#goapreservationmap","type":"content","content":"Resource tracking per-domain target reservations. Inspect via BRP to see which targets are claimed by which agents."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Reservation Policy","anchor":"#reservation-policy","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Reservation Policy","anchor":"#reservation-policy","type":"content","content":"Opt-in per-domain target coordination. Enable via:"},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`cost_penalty: u32`","anchor":"#cost-penalty-u32","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`cost_penalty: u32`","anchor":"#cost-penalty-u32","type":"content","content":"Default: 100 Extra cost added to target candidates reserved by another agent. Higher values make the planner strongly prefer unreserved targets."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`hard_block: bool`","anchor":"#hard-block-bool","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`hard_block: bool`","anchor":"#hard-block-bool","type":"content","content":"Default: false If true, reserved targets are excluded from planning entirely instead of being penalized."},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`ttl_seconds: Option<f32>`","anchor":"#ttl-seconds-option-f32","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`ttl_seconds: Option<f32>`","anchor":"#ttl-seconds-option-f32","type":"content","content":"Default: Some(10.0) Reservation lifetime in seconds. Expired reservations are reaped during GoapSystems::Cleanup. None means reservations persist until explicitly released (plan invalidation, goal completion, or agent deactivation)."},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","type":"title"},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"Debugging","anchor":"","type":"content","content":"Runtime visibility is a first-class requirement for saddle-ai-goap."},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"What To Inspect","anchor":"#what-to-inspect","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"What To Inspect","anchor":"#what-to-inspect","type":"content","content":"At minimum, every live agent exposes: - current goal - planner status - plan chain - active target bindings - last invalidation reason - deferred invalidation (if set, explains why a replan is pending behind a non-interruptible action) - sensed symbolic state - runtime counters - reserved targets These are available through GoapDebugSnapshot and the full GoapRuntime component."},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"Messages","anchor":"#messages","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"Messages","anchor":"#messages","type":"content","content":"High-value runtime messages: - GoalChanged - PlanStarted - PlanCompleted - PlanFailed - PlanInvalidated - ActionDispatched - ActionCancelled - ActionExecutionReport These are intentionally coarse-grained. The runtime does not emit per-frame chatter by default."},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"BRP-Friendly Types","anchor":"#brp-friendly-types","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"BRP-Friendly Types","anchor":"#brp-friendly-types","type":"content","content":"Useful BRP targets: - saddleaigoap::components::GoapAgent - saddleaigoap::components::GoapRuntime - saddleaigoap::debug::GoapDebugSnapshot - saddleaigoap::resources::GoapPlannerScheduler - saddleaigoap::resources::GoapGlobalSensorCache - saddleaigoap::reservations::GoapReservationMap The debug snapshot is the fastest way to answer \\"what is this agent trying to do right now?\\" The full runtime component is better when you need sensor timing, counters, or the active action ticket."},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"Crate-Local Lab","anchor":"#crate-local-lab","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"Crate-Local Lab","anchor":"#crate-local-lab","type":"content","content":"The recommended live debugging target is saddle-ai-goap-lab."},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"E2E scenarios","anchor":"#e2e-scenarios","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"E2E scenarios","anchor":"#e2e-scenarios","type":"content","content":"Scenario intent: - smokelaunch planner boots and both agents acquire a plan - goapsmoke alias behavior for the default planner overlay capture - goapreplan guard loses a target, invalidates, replans, and resolves the fallback - goapworker_cycle worker loses workstation availability, invalidates, replans, and eventually delivers Each scenario combines screenshots with at least one hard runtime assertion."},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"BRP Workflow","anchor":"#brp-workflow","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"BRP Workflow","anchor":"#brp-workflow","type":"content","content":"Questions these commands answer quickly: - Which entities are planners? - Which goal is active? - Which action is currently dispatched? - Which sensor cache revision is live? - Is the planner queue backing up? - Which targets are reserved and by whom? - Is a soft invalidation deferred behind a non-interruptible action?"},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"Reading The Snapshot","anchor":"#reading-the-snapshot","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"Reading The Snapshot","anchor":"#reading-the-snapshot","type":"content","content":"GoapDebugSnapshot fields: - currentgoal current goal name or None - plannerstatus human-readable PlannerStatus - planchain ordered plan with the current cursor marked - activetargets active bound targets rendered as slot => label - lastinvalidation last explicit invalidation reason - sensedstate compact symbolic state dump - counters aggregate plan, invalidation, and expansion counters"},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"Common Failure Modes","anchor":"#common-failure-modes","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"Agent never plans","anchor":"#agent-never-plans","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"Agent never plans","anchor":"#agent-never-plans","type":"content","content":"Check: - the entity has both GoapAgent and GoapRuntime - the selected goal is valid - at least one action can satisfy the goal - GoapPlannerScheduler.queue_depth is not stuck behind a tiny per-frame budget"},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"Plan keeps invalidating","anchor":"#plan-keeps-invalidating","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"Plan keeps invalidating","anchor":"#plan-keeps-invalidating","type":"content","content":"Check: - lastinvalidation - sensor intervals and invalidation messages - whether replanonsensedstate_change is too aggressive for the domain - whether target providers are returning unstable candidate sets"},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"Planner keeps failing the same goal","anchor":"#planner-keeps-failing-the-same-goal","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"Planner keeps failing the same goal","anchor":"#planner-keeps-failing-the-same-goal","type":"content","content":"Check: - whether the current goal is still valid when no action can satisfy it - whether sensors are actually changing revision after the world changes - whether the failed-plan retry gate is intentionally holding the goal until a relevant fact changes"},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"Action dispatches but nothing happens","anchor":"#action-dispatches-but-nothing-happens","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"Action dispatches but nothing happens","anchor":"#action-dispatches-but-nothing-happens","type":"content","content":"Check: - that a game-side system reads ActionDispatched - that it replies with ActionExecutionReport - that the action ticket in the report matches the active action ticket"},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"Sensor cache looks stale","anchor":"#sensor-cache-looks-stale","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"Sensor cache looks stale","anchor":"#sensor-cache-looks-stale","type":"content","content":"Check: - GoapGlobalSensorCache revisions - per-sensor nextdueseconds and lastrunseconds - whether the game should send InvalidateLocalSensors or InvalidateGlobalSensors"},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"Action never completes / replan keeps deferring","anchor":"#action-never-completes-replan-keeps-deferring","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"Action never completes / replan keeps deferring","anchor":"#action-never-completes-replan-keeps-deferring","type":"content","content":"Check: - ActiveAction.interruptible is false and holding completion - GoapRuntime.deferred_invalidation is set (indicates a pending soft invalidation) - whether the action executor has legitimately not reported Success or Failure yet - sensor intervals — frequent refreshes on non-interruptible actions queue deferred invalidations that pile up"},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"Two agents target the same entity","anchor":"#two-agents-target-the-same-entity","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Debugging","slug":"/docs/debugging/","heading":"Two agents target the same entity","anchor":"#two-agents-target-the-same-entity","type":"content","content":"Check: - whether the domain has a reservationpolicy set - GoapReservationMap for current reservations per domain - whether costpenalty is high enough to dissuade competing agents - whether hard_block should be enabled instead"},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","type":"title"},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"Planning Model","anchor":"","type":"content","content":"saddle-ai-goap plans over symbolic facts, not raw ECS snapshots."},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"World-State Model","anchor":"#world-state-model","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"World-State Model","anchor":"#world-state-model","type":"content","content":"The planner-visible state lives in GoapWorldState and is keyed by WorldKeyId entries from WorldStateSchema. Supported first-class value types: - Bool - Int - Target Why no built-in float or position facts in v1: - planner-visible state should stay compact and deterministic - float-heavy symbolic states are awkward to hash and compare - most spatial reasoning is better modeled as target selection plus context validation If a domain needs location-aware planning, prefer: - target providers returning TargetCandidate - TargetCandidate::debug_position for overlays and tooling - context validators or dynamic cost hooks for reachability, reservation, or travel heuristics"},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"Facts","anchor":"#facts","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"`FactCondition`","anchor":"#factcondition","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"`FactCondition`","anchor":"#factcondition","type":"content","content":"Supported comparisons: - equality / inequality - integer >= - integer <= - IsSet - IsUnset"},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"`FactEffect`","anchor":"#facteffect","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"`FactEffect`","anchor":"#facteffect","type":"content","content":"Supported symbolic effects: - set a fact - add to an integer fact - clear a fact"},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"`FactPatch`","anchor":"#factpatch","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"`FactPatch`","anchor":"#factpatch","type":"content","content":"Sensors emit FactPatch values to update symbolic memory."},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"Goals","anchor":"#goals","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"Goals","anchor":"#goals","type":"content","content":"Goals describe desired outcomes, not scripts. Each GoalDefinition contains: - desiredstate - fixed priority - optional dynamic relevance - optional validator - optional completion Selection model: 1. reject invalid goals 2. ignore already-complete goals 3. compute priority + dynamic relevance 4. pick the highest score 5. if preemptonbettergoal is enabled, switch only when the new goal beats the current one by goalswitchmargin"},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"Actions","anchor":"#actions","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"Actions","anchor":"#actions","type":"content","content":"Actions are symbolic planning units, not full gameplay stacks. Each ActionDefinition contains: - symbolic preconditions - symbolic effects - basecost - optional dynamiccost - optional context_validator - optional target specification - stable executor key - interruptible flag (default true) The planner reasons about the metadata above. The game owns the real execution that satisfies the action."},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"Target-Aware Actions","anchor":"#target-aware-actions","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"Target-Aware Actions","anchor":"#target-aware-actions","type":"content","content":"Target-aware actions use: - ActionTargetSpec symbolic slot name plus provider key - TargetProviderContext entity, domain, goal, current symbolic state, and action definition - TargetCandidate stable token, label, optional debug position, and optional cost bias Planning flow: 1. target provider returns candidates 2. each candidate becomes a PreparedActionVariant 3. optional context validation filters candidates 4. optional dynamic cost hook adjusts each candidate 5. the cheapest valid target-bound plan wins This is what lets one symbolic action represent \\"use workstation A\\" and \\"use workstation B\\" without making the planner blind to which target it actually chose."},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"Sensors","anchor":"#sensors","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"Sensors","anchor":"#sensors","type":"content","content":"Sensors are the boundary between rich ECS data and symbolic memory."},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"Local sensors","anchor":"#local-sensors","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"Local sensors","anchor":"#local-sensors","type":"content","content":"- run per agent - update agent-specific facts such as inventory, threat, or local cooldowns"},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"Global sensors","anchor":"#global-sensors","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"Global sensors","anchor":"#global-sensors","type":"content","content":"- run per domain - update shared facts or expensive cached data once for many agents Both sensor kinds: - support polling intervals - support explicit invalidation via messages - update runtime bookkeeping so BRP and overlays can inspect last run time, next due time, and notes"},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"Plan Search","anchor":"#plan-search","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"Plan Search","anchor":"#plan-search","type":"content","content":"The planner performs forward A over symbolic states. Heuristic (hmax): - for each unsatisfied goal condition, look up the minimum cost among actions whose effects can satisfy it (precomputed in ActionRelevanceMap) - return the maximum of those per-condition costs - admissible: never overestimates, since even an action satisfying multiple conditions still costs at least max(mincosti) Tie-breaking: - lower total estimated cost first - then lower path cost - then shallower depth - then action declaration order / target candidate order - then insertion order That ordering keeps results deterministic for the same inputs."},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"Replanning Policy","anchor":"#replanning-policy","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"Replanning Policy","anchor":"#replanning-policy","type":"content","content":"The runtime distinguishes several invalidation paths: - RequiredFactChanged remaining step precondition no longer matches - TargetInvalidated chosen target vanished or no longer passes context validation - ActionFailed execution reported failure - HigherPriorityGoal goal selection chose a better goal - SensorRefresh a newer sensor revision made the current plan or in-flight planning session stale and the agent is configured to react to that - GoalNoLongerValid goal validator failed - GoalCompleted goal finished - Manual external system explicitly invalidated the planner Default execution policy: - keep the current action alive while it is Running or Waiting - invalidate immediately if the action\'s current target disappears - invalidate immediately if the current step\'s required facts stop matching - between actions, optionally invalidate on SensorRefresh - after PlanFailed, hold that failure until the goal changes or sensors advance to a newer revision, instead of retrying the same impossible search every frame"},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"Execution Handoff","anchor":"#execution-handoff","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"Execution Handoff","anchor":"#execution-handoff","type":"content","content":"Execution is message-driven. Planner to game: - ActionDispatched Game to planner: - ActionExecutionReport::Running - ActionExecutionReport::Waiting - ActionExecutionReport::Success - ActionExecutionReport::Failure - ActionExecutionReport::Cancelled That boundary keeps the crate generic. A game can resolve an action through movement code, animation code, network RPCs, or a custom worker system without changing the planner."},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"World-State Hashing","anchor":"#world-state-hashing","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"World-State Hashing","anchor":"#world-state-hashing","type":"content","content":"GoapWorldState maintains an incrementally-updated Zobrist hash. Each setraw, clear, ensurelen, and overlay mutation XORs out the old slot hash and XORs in the new one. The Hash trait uses the cached u64 directly, and PartialEq fast-rejects on hash mismatch before comparing elements. This reduces per-node HashMap operations in the planner from O(keys) to O(1) average."},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"Target Reservations in Planning","anchor":"#target-reservations-in-planning","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"Planning Model","slug":"/docs/planning-model/","heading":"Target Reservations in Planning","anchor":"#target-reservations-in-planning","type":"content","content":"When GoapDomainDefinition.reservationpolicy is set, the planning problem construction phase checks each target candidate against GoapReservationMap. Targets reserved by other agents receive costpenalty additional cost (or are skipped with hard_block: true). This steers the planner toward unreserved targets without hard-gating the ECS. Reservations are acquired on plan acceptance and released on plan invalidation or completion."}]');export{e as default};
